    <h3>NoSql Database plugin</h3>
    <hr/>
    <p>
        <strong>NoSqlPlugin</strong> is a plugin that enables to setup and verify state of your nosql database system (like MongoDB)
    </p>
    <figure class="figure">
        <canvas class="nomnoml container" from="/specs/nosql/nosqldb.nomnoml"/>
        <figcaption class="figure-caption text-center">Exam integration with NoSql DB</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h4>Usage</h4>
    <p>1. Add dependency <pre class="doc-code language-java"><code>testImplementation "io.github.adven27:exam-nosql:{{version}}"</code></pre></p>
    <p>2. Configure and attach the <a cc:run="concordion" href="nosql/NoSqlPlugin.xhtml">NoSqlPlugin</a></p>

    <h4>Commands</h4>
    <p>
        There are commands for setting up and verifying and cleaning up database state.
        Also there is a command to just show current database state.
    </p>

    <h5>Set up NoSql Database</h5>

    <dl>
        <dt><code><a cc:run="concordion" href="nosql/nosqlset/NoSqlSet.xhtml">nosql-set</a></code></dt>
        <dd>
            <p>Creates and applies a dataset for specified collection from file or directly from your specification:</p>
            <pre class="doc-code language-xml"><code>
            <![CDATA[
                <e:nosql-set collection="MY_COLLECTION" from="/data/nosql/example.json"/>
            ]]>
            </code></pre>
            <pre class="doc-code language-xml"><code>
                <![CDATA[
                <e:nosql-set collection="MY_COLLECTION">
                    <e:doc>
                        [
                            {
                                "field1": "value1",
                                "field2": {
                                    "innerField1": "innerValue1"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "field2": "value2",
                                "field3": {
                                    "innerField2": "innerValue2"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    </e:doc>
                </e:nosql-set>
                ]]>
            </code></pre>
        </dd>
